{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"weekOfYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GLib","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE10weekOfYearSivp","title":"weekOfYear"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week number for the week containing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The ISO 8601 week number is the same for every day of the week (from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Moday through Sunday).  That can produce some unusual results"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(described below).","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol\/weekOfYear","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekOfYear"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The first week of the year is week 1.  This is the week that contains","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the first Thursday of the year.  Equivalently, this is the first week","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that has more than 4 of its days falling within the calendar year."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The value 0 is never returned by this function.  Days contained","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"within a year but occurring before the first ISO 8601 week of that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"year are considered as being contained in the last week of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"previous year.  Similarly, the final days of a calendar year may be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"considered as being part of the first ISO 8601 week of the next year","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if 4 or more days of that week are contained within the new year.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol\/weekofyear"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeProtocol/weekOfYear":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol\/weekofyear","role":"symbol","title":"weekOfYear","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekOfYear"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol\/weekOfYear","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week number for the week containing ","type":"text"},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The ISO 8601 week number is the same for every day of the week (from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Moday through Sunday).  That can produce some unusual results","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(described below).","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeProtocol":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GDateTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"into a single structure."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTimeProtocol"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTimeProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"DateTimeProtocol"}}}